create_python_api.py script generates init.py files that define TensorFlow API.
Currently, we don't have print_function included in these files because it is not a part of TensorFlow API.

What is the usecase for having print_function available in TensorFlow API? Can users of TensorFlow API just import it before tensorflow?

body:
create_python_api.py script generates __init__.py files that define TensorFlow API.
Currently, we don't have print_function included in these files because it is not a part of TensorFlow API.

What is the usecase for having print_function available in TensorFlow API? Can users of TensorFlow API just import it before tensorflow?
